Docker commmands

++++++++++++++++++++++++

 <!-- create a Image of an docker -->

<!-- Command :  -->
 docker build -t sumukh-customer ./customers     
 
 <!-- -t : tag the image with its name "sumukh-customer" , 
 ./customer : path of Dockerfile -->


++++++++++++++++++++++++

 <!-- create a Container of an image -->

<!-- Command :  -->
docker run -p 8002:3000 sumukh-customer

<!-- -p : denote to the port
8002: browser port when ever the docker run the application, docker will use port 8002  -->




++++++++++++++++++++++++

 <!-- list of docker image -->

<!-- Command :  -->
docker image ls




++++++++++++++++++++++++

 <!-- delete  the  docker image -->

<!-- Command :  -->
docker image rm  0bed5f0d0bc0

<!-- rm: remove image
0bed5f0d0bc0: image ID -->



